{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17637336","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17637336"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:41:15+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:41:15+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17651"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17651","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17651"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10365"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75455"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10365","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10365"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17651"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60965"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4948"},{"type":"tags","id":"7695"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24233"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24239"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75455","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75455"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EBiostatistics plays a crucial role in medical research and evidence-based medicine.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes biostatistics?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["The collection of health data from populations","The use of computers to model biological systems","The study of mathematical patterns in nature","The application of statistical methods to biological and medical research","The statistical analysis of genetic sequences"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct definition is that biostatistics is the \u003Cstrong\u003Eapplication of statistical methods to biological and medical research\u003C/strong\u003E. This encompasses the design of studies, collection and analysis of data, and interpretation of results in medical and biological contexts.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe study of mathematical patterns in nature\u003C/strong\u003E - This better describes biomathematics, which focuses on mathematical modelling of biological phenomena\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe collection of health data from populations\u003C/strong\u003E - This describes epidemiology, which is related to but distinct from biostatistics\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe use of computers to model biological systems\u003C/strong\u003E - This describes bioinformatics or computational biology\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe statistical analysis of genetic sequences\u003C/strong\u003E - This is too narrow and describes only one specific application of biostatistics\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EBiostatistics provides the methodological foundation for quantitative research in medicine and biology, helping researchers design studies and draw valid conclusions from data.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Biostatistics is the application of statistical methods to biological and medical research data.","Biostatistics helps researchers design studies, analyse data, and draw valid conclusions from medical research.","Key components of biostatistics include study design, data collection, analysis, and interpretation of results."],"references":["Sullivan LM. Essentials of biostatistics in public health. 3rd ed. Burlington (MA): Jones \u0026 Bartlett Learning; 2018.","Daw